   John Major, who was endorsed by Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher as her successor and heir, was elected today as leader of the Conservative Party and will become prime minister. Major fell two votes short of the needed majority, but his opponents conceded defeat and Conservative Party officials declared him elected . Major, 47, her chancellor of the Exchequer, is the youngest person to be elected Britain's prime minister since the 19th Century .
